Multivariate Plots Section

These plots(x is LenderYield, y is EstimatedEffectiveYield, faceted by ProsperScore) clearly show that, generally LenderYield has a positive ratio relationship with EstimatedEffectiveYield, and EstimatedEffectiveYield will decrease a little with ProsperScores increasing.

By this graph, it is obvious that, with higher Loan Current Days Delinquent, the customers Estimated Effective Yield will siginificantly drop down. But, if this customer has high ProsperScore, the Estimated Effective Yield will change very little with Loan Current Days Delinquent.It can be illstrated as with higher ProsperScore, even if this customer has loan delinquent, bank can still estimate a high Effective Yield.

By this graph, we can see, with higher loan original amount, the estimated effective yield is relatively low, and with higher prosper score, the estimated effective yield will become lower.

Reflection

For this project, my most siginificant obstacle is to find what is the main feature. Finally I decided EstimatedEffectiveYield as my main feature because it is related with profit the bank can earn for each customer. However, there still are some other features very important, for example, Loan Current Days Delinquent, which may show if this customer can pay his/her credit or not.

So, for futures further investigation, I would like to explore other features from other perspective, and at last make a fine predictive model to decide should the bank loan money to some customer or not.
